{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1359,"text":"Great things happen at intersections."},{"time":4800,"text":"In fact, I would argue\nthat some of the most interesting things"},{"time":8039,"text":"of the human experience\noccur at the intersections,"},{"time":11840,"text":"in the liminal space,"},{"time":13520,"text":"where by liminal\nI mean the space in-between."},{"time":17600,"text":"There's freedom in that in-between,"},{"time":20320,"text":"freedom to create from the indefiniteness\nof not-quite-here, not-quite-there,"},{"time":26120,"text":"a new self-definition."},{"time":29360,"text":"Some of the great intersections\nof the world come to mind,"},{"time":32400,"text":"like the Arc de Triomphe in Paris,"},{"time":34640,"text":"or Times Square in New York City,"},{"time":37120,"text":"both bustling with the excitement\nof a seemingly endless stream of people."},{"time":43080,"text":"Other intersections,"},{"time":44600,"text":"like the Edmund Pettus Bridge\nin Selma, Alabama,"},{"time":47480,"text":"or Canfield Drive and Copper Creek Court\nin Ferguson, Missouri, also come to mind"},{"time":53200,"text":"because of the tremendous energy\nat the intersection of human beings,"},{"time":58160,"text":"ideologies and the ongoing\nstruggle for justice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63120,"text":"Beyond the physical\nlandscape of our planet,"},{"time":65480,"text":"some of the most famous celestial images\nare of intersections."},{"time":69520,"text":"Stars are born at the messy\nintersection of gas and dust,"},{"time":73920,"text":"instigated by gravity's irrevocable pull."},{"time":77440,"text":"Stars die by this same intersection,\nthis time flung outward"},{"time":81800,"text":"in a violent collision of smaller atoms,"},{"time":84200,"text":"intersecting and efficiently fusing\ninto altogether new and heavier things."},{"time":90840,"text":"We can all think of intersections\nthat have special meaning to us."},{"time":95760,"text":"To be intersectional, then,"},{"time":97600,"text":"is to occupy a position\nat an intersection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102600,"text":"I've lived the entirety of my life\nin the in-between,"},{"time":107000,"text":"in the liminal space\nbetween dreams and reality,"},{"time":111280,"text":"race and gender,"},{"time":113600,"text":"poverty and plenty,"},{"time":115640,"text":"science and society."},{"time":118720,"text":"I am both black and a woman."},{"time":121680,"text":"Like the birth of stars in the heavenlies,"},{"time":124040,"text":"this robust combination of knowing\nresults in a shining example"},{"time":128560,"text":"of the explosive fusion of identities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132080,"text":"I am also an astrophysicist."},{"time":135200,"text":"I study blazars, supermassive,\nhyperactive black holes"},{"time":140280,"text":"that sit at the centers\nof massive galaxies"},{"time":142960,"text":"and shoot out jets\nnearby those black holes"},{"time":145840,"text":"at speeds approaching the speed of light"},{"time":148600,"text":"in a process we are still trying\nto completely understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153600,"text":"I have dreamed\nof becoming an astrophysicist"},{"time":156720,"text":"since I was 12 years old."},{"time":159200,"text":"I had no idea that at that time,"},{"time":161600,"text":"according to Dr. Jamie Alexander's archive\nof African-American women in physics,"},{"time":167320,"text":"only 18 black women in the United States\nhad ever earned a PhD"},{"time":171680,"text":"in a physics-related discipline,"},{"time":173680,"text":"and that the first black woman to graduate\nwith a PhD in an astronomy-related field"},{"time":178360,"text":"did so just one year before my birth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182880,"text":"As I journeyed along my path,"},{"time":184720,"text":"I encountered the best and worst\nof life at an intersection:"},{"time":189600,"text":"the tremendous opportunity to self-define,"},{"time":192440,"text":"the collision of expectation\nand experience,"},{"time":196000,"text":"the exhilaration\nof victorious breakthroughs"},{"time":198760,"text":"and, sometimes,"},{"time":200480,"text":"the explosive pain of regeneration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204360,"text":"I began my college experience\njust after my family had fallen apart."},{"time":210120,"text":"Our financial situation disintegrated"},{"time":212760,"text":"just after my father's\ndeparture from our lives."},{"time":216200,"text":"This thrust my mother, my sister and I"},{"time":219120,"text":"out of the relative comfort\nof middle-class life"},{"time":222120,"text":"and into the almost constant struggle\nto make ends meet."},{"time":226520,"text":"Thus, I was one of roughly\n60 percent of women of color"},{"time":230360,"text":"who find finances to be a major barrier\nto their educational goals."},{"time":235240,"text":"Thankfully, Norfolk State University\nprovided me with full funding,"},{"time":238880,"text":"and I was able to achieve\nmy bachelor's in physics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242840,"text":"After graduation, and despite knowing\nthat I wanted a PhD in astrophysics,"},{"time":247880,"text":"I fell through the cracks."},{"time":250080,"text":"It was a poster that saved my dream,"},{"time":253200,"text":"and some really incredible\npeople and programs."},{"time":257000,"text":"The American Physical Society\nhad this beautiful poster"},{"time":260640,"text":"encouraging students of color\nto become physicists."},{"time":264360,"text":"It was striking to me\nbecause it featured a young black girl,"},{"time":267880,"text":"probably around 12 years old,"},{"time":269680,"text":"looking studiously\nat some physics equations."},{"time":274200,"text":"I remember thinking"},{"time":276400,"text":"I was looking directly back\nat the little girl"},{"time":279120,"text":"who first dared to dream this dream."},{"time":281960,"text":"I immediately wrote to the Society"},{"time":283920,"text":"and requested my personal\ncopy of the poster,"},{"time":287840,"text":"which to this day\nstill hangs in my office."},{"time":291240,"text":"I described to them in the email\nmy educational path,"},{"time":294120,"text":"and my desire to find myself again\nin pursuit of the PhD."},{"time":299040,"text":"They directed me to the Fisk-Vanderbilt\nUniversity Bridge Program,"},{"time":302800,"text":"itself an intersection\nof the master's and PhD degrees"},{"time":306600,"text":"at two institutions."},{"time":309560,"text":"After two years out of school,\nthey accepted me into the program,"},{"time":313080,"text":"and I found myself again\non the path to the PhD."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317520,"text":"After receiving my master's at Fisk,"},{"time":320000,"text":"I went on to Yale to complete my PhD."},{"time":323360,"text":"Once I was physically occupying\nthe space that would ultimately give way"},{"time":327520,"text":"to my childhood aspirations,"},{"time":329520,"text":"I anticipated a smooth glide to the PhD."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":334720,"text":"It became immediately apparent"},{"time":336800,"text":"that not everyone was thrilled\nto have that degree of liminality"},{"time":340840,"text":"in their space."},{"time":342480,"text":"I was ostracized by many of my classmates,"},{"time":345560,"text":"one of whom went so far as to invite me\nto \"do what I really came here to do\""},{"time":350920,"text":"as he pushed all the dirty dishes\nfrom our meal in front of me to clean up."},{"time":356560,"text":"I wish that were an isolated occurrence,"},{"time":359480,"text":"but for many women of color"},{"time":361240,"text":"in science, technology, engineering,\nand mathematics, or STEM,"},{"time":367080,"text":"this is something they have long endured."},{"time":369680,"text":"One hundred percent\nof the 60 women of color"},{"time":372840,"text":"interviewed in a recent study\nby Joan C. Williams at UC Hastings"},{"time":377200,"text":"reported facing racialized gender bias,"},{"time":380600,"text":"including being mistaken\nfor the janitorial staff."},{"time":385280,"text":"This mistaken identity was not reported"},{"time":388200,"text":"by any of the white women\ninterviewed for this study,"},{"time":390760,"text":"which comprised 557 women in total."},{"time":395560,"text":"While there is nothing inherently wrong\nwith a janitorial position,"},{"time":399640,"text":"and in fact my forefathers and foremothers\nwere able to attend college"},{"time":403080,"text":"because many of their parents\nworked these jobs,"},{"time":405960,"text":"it was a clear attempt\nto put me in my place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410840,"text":"While there was certainly\nthe acute pain of the encounter,"},{"time":414080,"text":"the real issue is that my appearance"},{"time":416680,"text":"can tell anyone anything about my ability."},{"time":421240,"text":"Beyond that, though, it underscores"},{"time":423600,"text":"that the women of color in STEM\ndo not experience the same set of barriers"},{"time":429600,"text":"that just women\nor just people of color face."},{"time":433720,"text":"That's why today I want to highlight\nwomen of color in STEM,"},{"time":437600,"text":"who are inexorably, unapologetically"},{"time":440520,"text":"living as the inseparable\nsum of identities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":445600,"text":"STEM itself is an intersectional term,"},{"time":448600,"text":"such that its true richness\ncannot be appreciated"},{"time":451880,"text":"without considering\nthe liminal space between disciplines."},{"time":455760,"text":"Science, the pursuit\nof understanding the physical world"},{"time":458560,"text":"by way of chemistry, physics, biology,"},{"time":461680,"text":"cannot be accomplished\nin the absence of mathematics."},{"time":465480,"text":"Engineering requires the application\nof basic science and math"},{"time":469560,"text":"to the lived experience."},{"time":471600,"text":"Technology sits firmly\non the foundation of math,"},{"time":475320,"text":"engineering and science."},{"time":477680,"text":"Math itself serves\nthe critical role of Rosetta Stone,"},{"time":481720,"text":"decoding and encoding\nthe physical principles of the world."},{"time":486480,"text":"STEM is utterly incomplete\nwithout each individual piece."},{"time":491440,"text":"This is to say nothing\nof the enrichment that is realized"},{"time":494840,"text":"when STEM is combined\nwith other disciplines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498480,"text":"The purpose for this talk is twofold:"},{"time":501080,"text":"first, to say directly to every black,\nLatina, indigenous, First Nation"},{"time":506840,"text":"or any other woman or girl"},{"time":508880,"text":"who finds herself resting\nat the blessed intersection"},{"time":512120,"text":"of race and gender,"},{"time":514159,"text":"that you can be anything you want to be."},{"time":518159,"text":"My personal hope is\nthat you'll become an astrophysicist,"},{"time":521679,"text":"but beyond that, anything you want."},{"time":524760,"text":"Do not think for one minute"},{"time":527840,"text":"that because you are who you are,"},{"time":530120,"text":"you cannot be\nwho you imagine yourself to be."},{"time":533680,"text":"Hold fast to those dreams"},{"time":536160,"text":"and let them carry you\ninto a world you can't even imagine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540640,"text":"Secondly, among the most\npressing issues of our time,"},{"time":544400,"text":"most now find\ntheir intersection with STEM."},{"time":548040,"text":"We have as a global society solved"},{"time":550080,"text":"most of the single-faceted\nissues of our time."},{"time":553800,"text":"Those that remain\nrequire a thorough investigation"},{"time":557280,"text":"of the liminal space between disciplines"},{"time":560080,"text":"to create the multifaceted\nsolutions of tomorrow."},{"time":564520,"text":"Who better to solve these liminal problems"},{"time":567640,"text":"than those who have faced\ntheir whole lives at the intersections."},{"time":572000,"text":"We as thought leaders and decision makers"},{"time":574960,"text":"must push past\nthe first steps of diversity"},{"time":578400,"text":"and into the richer\nand more robust territory"},{"time":581720,"text":"of full inclusion and equal opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585760,"text":"One of my favorite examples\nof liminal excellence"},{"time":588840,"text":"comes from the late Dr. Claudia Alexander,"},{"time":591720,"text":"a black woman plasma physicist,"},{"time":593480,"text":"who passed away this past July\nafter a 10-year bout with breast cancer."},{"time":598560,"text":"She was a NASA project scientist\nwho spearheaded the NASA side"},{"time":602680,"text":"of the Rosetta mission,"},{"time":604160,"text":"which became famous this year\nfor landing a rover on a comet,"},{"time":608640,"text":"and the 1.5 billion dollar\nGalileo mission to Jupiter,"},{"time":613160,"text":"two high-profile scientific victories"},{"time":616160,"text":"for NASA, the United States\nand the world."},{"time":620280,"text":"Dr. Alexander said it this way:"},{"time":623000,"text":"\"I'm used to walking between two cultures."},{"time":625720,"text":"For me, it's among the purposes of my life"},{"time":628880,"text":"to take us from states of ignorance\nto states of understanding"},{"time":632520,"text":"with bold exploration\nthat you can't do every day.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":636920,"text":"This shows exactly\nthe power of a liminal person."},{"time":640720,"text":"She had the technical ability to spearhead"},{"time":643120,"text":"some of the most ambitious\nspace missions of our time,"},{"time":646240,"text":"and she perfectly understood her place"},{"time":649600,"text":"of being exactly who she was\nin any place she was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654240,"text":"Jessica Matthews, inventor\nof the SOCCKET line of sports products,"},{"time":657880,"text":"like soccer balls, that generate\nrenewable energy as you play with them,"},{"time":661880,"text":"said it this way:"},{"time":663760,"text":"\"A major part of invention\nisn't just creating things,"},{"time":667240,"text":"it's understanding people"},{"time":669080,"text":"and understanding the systems\nthat make this world.\""},{"time":673320,"text":"The reason I tell my story"},{"time":675160,"text":"and the story of Dr. Alexander\nand Jessica Matthews"},{"time":678240,"text":"is because they are fundamentally\nintersectional stories,"},{"time":682120,"text":"the stories of lives lived at the nexus\nof race, gender and innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688760,"text":"Despite implicit and explicit questions\nof my right to be in an elite space,"},{"time":694400,"text":"I'm proud to report that when I graduated,"},{"time":697000,"text":"I was the first black woman\nto earn a PhD in astrophysics"},{"time":700480,"text":"in Yale's then 312-year history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703600,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":709520,"text":"I am now part of a small but growing cadre\nof women of color in STEM"},{"time":714960,"text":"who are poised to bring new perspectives\nand new ideas to life"},{"time":719000,"text":"on the most pressing issues of our time:"},{"time":721800,"text":"things like educational inequities,"},{"time":724000,"text":"police brutality, HIV/AIDS,\nclimate change, genetic editing,"},{"time":730000,"text":"artificial intelligence\nand Mars exploration."},{"time":733400,"text":"This is to say nothing of the things\nwe haven't even thought of yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737720,"text":"Women of color in STEM\noccupy some of the toughest"},{"time":741240,"text":"and most exciting sociotechnological\nissues of our time."},{"time":746040,"text":"Thus, we are uniquely positioned"},{"time":748400,"text":"to contribute to\nand drive these conversations"},{"time":751840,"text":"in ways that are more inclusive\nof a wider variety of lived experience."},{"time":757000,"text":"This outlook can be expanded\nto the many intersectional people"},{"time":760600,"text":"whose experiences, positive and negative,"},{"time":763680,"text":"enrich the conversations\nin ways that outmatch"},{"time":766760,"text":"even the best-resourced homogenous groups."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770880,"text":"This is not a request\nborn out of a desire to fit in."},{"time":774800,"text":"It's a reminder that we cannot get\nto the best possible outcomes"},{"time":779320,"text":"for the totality of humanity"},{"time":781520,"text":"without precisely this collaboration,"},{"time":784000,"text":"this bringing together of the liminal,"},{"time":786560,"text":"the differently lived,\ndistinctly experienced"},{"time":790080,"text":"and disparately impacted."},{"time":792640,"text":"Simply put, we cannot be\nthe most excellent expression"},{"time":796680,"text":"of our collective genius"},{"time":798480,"text":"without the full measure\nof humanity brought to bear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803240,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}